her Woman (2014 film)|The Other Woman]]''\n| Mark King\n| [[Nick Cassavetes]]\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n! scope=row | ''[[A Second Chance (film)|A Second Chance]]''\n| Andreas\n| [[Susanne Bier]]\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n! scope=row | ''Upstart''\n| {{N/A}}\n|\n| Executive producer\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n! scope=row | ''Livsforkortelses Ekspert''\n| {{N/A}}\n|\n| Producer\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| 2015\n! scope=row | ''Klovn Forever''\n| Himself\n| Mikkel N\u00f8rgaard\n| Cameo\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |2016\n! scope=row | ''[[Gods of Egypt (film)|Gods of Egypt]]''\n| [[Horus]]\n| [[Alex Proyas]]\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n! scope=row | ''Chicken / Egg''\n| Kenneth\n| [[James D'Arcy]]\n| Short film\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://prod1.agileticketing.net/websales/pages/info.aspx?evtinfo=117875~95c7d792-cc78-409e-9556-3d769472d98b&|title=Chicken / Egg|website=Nashville Film Festival|access-date=2017-05-27}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |2017\n! scope=row | ''[[Small Crimes]]''\n| Joe Denton\n| [[E. L. Katz]]\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|last1=Keslassy|first1=Elsa|first2=Brent|last2=Lang|title=Netflix Buys Nikolaj Coster-Waldau\u2019s \u2018Small Crimes\u2019 Ahead of SXSW Debut (Exclusive)|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/netflix-small-crimes-sxsw-nikolaj-coster-waldau-1201978975/|accessdate=3 April 2017|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=6 February 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row align=\"left\"| ''3 Things''\n| Mikael\n| Jens Dahl\n| Executive producer\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\":0\" />\n|-\n! scope=row align=\"left\"| ''[[Shot Caller (film)|Shot Caller]]''\n| Jacob 'Money' Harlon\n| Ric Roman Waugh\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|last1=Busch|first1=Anita|title=Relativity Plunks Down $3M To Pick Up Bold Films\u2019 \u2018Shot Caller\u2019 With \u2018Games Of Thrones\u2019 Actor I