l-status=live |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=6|2013\n| [[40th People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite TV Anti-Hero\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/477644/glee-katy-perry-lead-people-s-choice-award-nominations-2-broke-girls-kat-dennings-and-beth-behrs-to-host |title=Glee, Katy Perry Lead People's Choice Award Nominations, 2 Broke Girls' Kat Dennings and Beth Behrs to Host |publisher=E! Online |date=November 5, 2013 |accessdate=November 5, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Award]]\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Supporting Actor in a Drama Series|Best Supporting Actor in a Drama Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Big Bang, Horror Story, Parks & Rec, Good Wife, The Americans Lead Critics Choice Nominations|publisher=TVLine|url=http://tvline.com/2013/05/22/critics-choice-television-nominations-3rd-annual/|date=May 22, 2013|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Satellite Awards]]\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Series, Miniseries or Television Film|Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Series, Miniseries or Television Film]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-international-press-academy-announces-nominations-for-the-18th-annual-satellite-awards-234075351.html|title=The International Press Academy Announces Nominations For The 18th Annual Satellite Awards\u2122|publisher=PR Newswire|date=December 2, 2013|accessdate=August 16, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actor on Television|Best Supporting Actor on Television]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/saturn-award-nominees-2014-gravity-hobbit-desolation-smaug/|title=Saturn Award Nominations Announced; GRAVITY and THE HOBBIT: THE DESOLATION OF SMAUG Lead with 8 Nominations Each|publisher=Collider|date=February 26, 2014|accessdate=August 16, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| Gold Derby Awards\n| Best Drama Supporting Actor\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldderby.com/article/2013/gold-derby-awards-breaking-bad-parks-recreation-entertainment-news-747882424/ |title='Breaking Bad,' \u2018Parks and Rec' win big at Gold Derby TV Awards! |publisher=Gold Derby |first=Daniel |last=Montgomery |date=September 18, 2013 |access-date=August 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009084620/http://www.goldderby.com/article/2013/gold-derby-awards-breaking-bad-parks-recreation-entertainment-news-747882424/ |archive-date=October 9, 2016 |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]\n| Best Ensemble in a Drama Series\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/12/sag-awards-2013-nominations-full-list/ |title=SAG Awards Nominations: \u201812 Years A Slave\u2019 And \u2018Breaking Bad\u2019 Lead Way |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=December 11, 2013 |access-date=March 29, 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20131211210823/http://www.deadline.com/2013/12/sag-awards-2013-nominations-full-list/ |archive-date=December 11, 2013 |url-status=live |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]\n| Best Ensemble in a Drama Series\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news | last=Hipes| first=Patrick | url=http://deadline.com/2014/12/sag-awards-nominations-2015-full-list-nominees-1201317757/|title=SAG Awards Nominations: 'Birdman' & 'Boyhood' Lead Film Side, HBO & 'Modern Family' Rule TV \u2013 Full List| website=Deadline Hollywood | date=December 10, 2014 | access-date=March 29, 2017 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150126230813/http://deadline.com/2014/12/sag-awards-nominations-2015-full-list-nominees-1201317757/|archive-date=January 26, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2015\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]\n| Best Ensemble in a Drama Series\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160822074856/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2016-sag-winners-complete-list-856945/item/outstanding-performance-by-a-female-846040 |archive-date=August 22, 2016|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2016-sag-winners-complete-list-856945/item/outstanding-performance-by-a-female-846040|title=SAG Awards: The Complete Winners List|work=The Hollywood Reporter|publisher=Lynne Segall|date=January 30, 2016|access-date=March 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Empire Awards]]\n| [[Empire Hero Award]] <small>(shared with cast)</small>\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.empireonline.com/awards2015/winners/hero.asp |title=The Jameson Empire Awards 2015 |website=[[Empireonline.com]] |publisher=[[Bauer Consumer Media]] |date=2015 |accessdate=1 April 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402111635/http://www.empireonline.com/awards2015/winners/hero.asp |archivedate=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]\n| Best Ensemble in a Drama Series\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170111005833/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/14/2017-sag-awards-nominations |archive-date=January 11, 2017|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/14/2017-sag-awards-nominations|title=SAG Awards nominations 2017: See the full list|first=Joey |last=Nolfi|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=December 14, 2016|access-date=March 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2017\n| [[Cinema of Denmark|Zulu Award]]\n| Best Actor\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tv.tv2.dk/zulu-awards/2017-01-10-stem-paa-aarets-skuespiller-afstemning-afsluttet|title=Stem P\u00e5 \u00c5rets Skuespiller - Afstemning afsluttet|date=January 10, 2017|accessdate=February 18, 2017|work=[[TV 2 (Denmark)|TV2]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|Nordisk Film Fond\n|[[Ove Sprog\u00f8e Award]]\n|\n|{{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.kamikposten.gl/2017/11/09/%F0%9F%87%A9%F0%9F%87%B0-isbjoernen-2017-er-uddelt-nikolaj-coster-waldau-modtog-ove-sprogoee-prisen/|title=\ud83c\udde9\ud83c\uddf0 ISBJ\u00d8RNEN 2017 er uddelt! Nikolaj Coster-Waldau modtog Ove Sprog\u00f8e Prisen|date=2017-11-09|work=KamikPosten.gl|access-date=2017-11-18|language=da-DK}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]\n| Best Ensemble in a Drama Series\n| rowspan=5|''Game of Thrones''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hipes|first1=Patrick|title=SAG Awards Nominations: \u2018Three Billboards\u2019 Tops Film List, Netflix Leads In TV|url=http://deadline.com/2017/12/2018-sag-awards-nominees-screen-actors-guild-nominations-1202225184/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=13 December 2017|date=13 December 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2018\n| [[44th Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n| Best Supporting Actor on a Television Series\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=\u2018Black Panther,\u2019 \u2018Walking Dead\u2019 Rule Saturn Awards Nominations|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/saturn-awards-nominations-2018-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/|website=Variety|accessdate=15 March 2018|date=15 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[70th Primetime Emmy Awards|Primetime Emmy Awards]]\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-emmy-nominations-list-see-all-the-nominees-1110785/item/writing-a-comedy-series-emmy-nominations-2018-1110796 |title=Emmys: Netflix Beats HBO With Most Nominations |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=July 12, 2018 |accessdate=July 12, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2019\n| [[45th Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actor on Television|Best Supporting Actor on Television]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mancuso |first1=Vinnie |title='Avengers: Endgame', 'Game of Thrones' Lead the 2019 Saturn Awards Nominations |url=http://collider.com/saturn-awards-nominations-2019/ |website=Collider |accessdate=16 July 2019 |date=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[71st Primetime Emmy Awards|Primetime Emmy Awards]]\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Biography}}\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Coster-Waldau, Nikolaj}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Danish male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish male actors]]\n[[Category:Danish film producers]]\n[[Category:Danish screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Danish male writers]]\n[[Category:Danish male film actors]]\n[[Category:Danish male television actors]]\n[[Category:People from Langeland Municipality]]\n[[Category:Danish male actors]]\n[[Category:Danish expatriates in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|Coster-Waldau|his wife, the former Miss Greenland|Nukaaka Coster-Waldau}}\n{{Short description|Danish actor and screenwriter}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Nikolaj Coster-Waldau\n| image              = Nikolaj Coster-Waldau by Gage Skidmore 2.jpg\n| caption            = Coster-Waldau at the 2019 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1970|7|27}}\n| birth_place        = [[Rudk\u00f8bing]], Denmark\n| residence          = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n[[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]]\n[[Rudk\u00f8bing]],  [[Denmark]] \n| alma_mater         = [[Danish National School of Performing Arts]]\n| occupation         = Actor, producer, screenwriter\n| years_active       = 1993\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Nukaaka Coster-Waldau|Sascha Nuk\u00e2ka Motzfeldt]]|1997}}\n| children           = 2\n}}\n\n'''Nikolaj Coster-Waldau''' ({{IPA-da|\u02c8neko\u02cclaj\u02c0 \u02c8k\u02b0\u0252st\u0250 \u02c8v\u00e6ltaw}}; born 27 July 1970) is a Danish actor, producer and screenwriter. He graduated from the [[Danish National School of Performing Arts]] in [[Copenhagen]] in 1993. Coster-Waldau's breakthrough performance in Denmark was his role in the film ''[[Nightwatch (1994 film)|Nightwatch]]'' (1994). Since then he has appeared in numerous films in his native Scandinavia and Europe in general, including ''[[Headhunters (film)|Headhunters]]'' (2011) and ''[[A Thousand Times Good Night]]'' (2013).\n\nIn the U.S, his debut film role was in the war film ''[[Black Hawk Down (film)|Black Hawk Down]]'' (2001), playing Medal of Honor recipient [[Gary Gordon]]. He then played Detective John Amsterdam in the short-lived [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] television series ''[[New Amsterdam (2008 TV series)|New Amsterdam]]'' (2008), as well as appearing as Frank Pike in the 2009 Fox television film ''[[Virtuality (TV series)|Virtuality]]'', originally intended as a pilot. He became widely known for his role as [[Jaime Lannister]] in the [[HBO]] fantasy series ''[[Game of Thrones]]'', for which he received [[Primetime Emmy Award]] nominations for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series]] in 2018 and 2019. He is a [[UNDP]] Goodwill Ambassador, drawing public attention to critical issues such as gender equality and climate change.\n\n==Early life==\nCoster-Waldau was born in [[Rudk\u00f8bing]], Denmark, the son of Hanne S\u00f8borg Coster, a [[librarian]],<ref name=details>{{cite web |url=http://www.details.com/culture-trends/cover-stars/201404/nikolaj-coster-waldau-interview-hbo-game-of-thrones-jaime-lannister/?currentPage=2 |title=Great Dane: Game of Thrones' Nikolaj Coster-Waldau |first=Benjamin |last=Svetkey |page=2 |date=1 April 2014 |website=Cond\u00e9 Nast |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150908075349/http://www.details.com/culture-trends/cover-stars/201404/nikolaj-coster-waldau-interview-hbo-game-of-thrones-jaime-lannister/?currentPage=2 |archivedate=8 September 2015 |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> and J\u00f8rgen Oscar Fritzer Waldau (died 1998). He has spoken in interviews about his father's problems with alcohol, as well as his parents' divorce.<ref name=details/> He has two older sisters, and was raised mainly by his mother.<ref name=\"Independent\">{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/my-secret-life-nikolaj-coster-waldau-42-actor-8533216.html |title=My Secret Life: Nikolaj Coster-Waldau, 42, actor |first=Charlie |last=Cooper |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |date=16 March 2013 |location=London, UK |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> He grew up in Tybjerg, a small village between [[Ringsted]] and [[N\u00e6stved]] in southern [[Zealand]].<ref name=details/><ref name=\"Independent\"/> Coster-Waldau was the youngest actor to enter the [[Danish National School of Theatre and Contemporary Dance]] (Danish: [[Statens Teaterskole]]), where he was educated from 1989 to 1993.\n\n==Career==\n===Early career and breakthrough (1993\u20132000)===\nCoster-Waldau made his stage debut as [[Laertes (Hamlet)|Laertes]] in ''[[Hamlet]]'' at the Betty Nansen Theater. His role in the film ''[[Nightwatch (1994 film)|Nightwatch]]'' (1994) brought him fame in his native country.<ref name=\"New Amsterdam Forever\">{{cite web |url=http://newamsterdam-forever.com/CastList/CastList.html |title=New Amsterdam Cast List |website=New Amsterdam : Forever |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714172220/http://newamsterdam-forever.com/CastList/CastList.html |archivedate=14 July 2011 |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> He then went on to play in Simon Staho's ''Wildside'' (1998), which he also cowrote, and starred in Danish films such as ''[[Misery Harbour]]'' (1999). He made his British d\u00e9but alongside Clive Owen, Jude Law and Mick Jagger in ''[[Bent (1997 film)|Bent]]'' (1997).<ref name=danskedatabase>{{cite web |url=http://www.danskefilm.dk/skuespiller/744.html |title=Nikolaj Coster Waldau |website=Den danske film database |accessdate=13 July 2016 |language=Danish}}</ref>\n\n=== Transition to United States film and television (2001\u20132010) ===\n[[File:Nikolaj Coster-Waldau.jpg|thumb|left|195px|Coster-Waldau at the 2011 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]]]\n\nIn 2001, he began his U.S. career in [[Ridley Scott]]'s ''[[Black Hawk Down (film)|Black Hawk Down]]'' as [[Medal of Honor]] recipient [[Gary Gordon]]. Coster-Waldau says \"My first U.S. movie was ''Black Hawk Down'' and a friend helped me put myself on tape up on the attic over my apartment in Copenhagen. We shipped it out and I got lucky.\"<ref name=\"myFanbase\">{{cite web |url=http://www.myfanbase.de/serien/interviews/?pid=13447 |title=Interview with Nikolaj Coster-Waldau |first=Nicole |last=Oebel |website=myfanbase.de |accessdate=24 February 2012}}</ref>\n\nCoster-Waldau used his success to take roles on both sides of the Atlantic, particularly his native [[Scandinavia]].<ref name=\"Claiming The Throne As HollyWood's New Leading Man\">{{cite journal |url=http://eadestination.com/nikolaj-coster-waldau |title=Nikolaj Coster-Waldau: Taking It All In Stride |date=May 2014 |journal=[[Destination (magazine)|Destination]] |pages=36\u201341 |accessdate=23 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe later landed a lead role in [[Michael Apted]]'s ''[[Enigma (2001 film)|Enigma]]'' and also appeared as a villain in the action film ''[[My Name is Modesty]]'' (based upon the ''[[Modesty Blaise]]'' comic strip). Scott brought Coster-Waldau back for his 2005 film ''[[Kingdom of Heaven (film)|Kingdom of Heaven]]''. [[Richard Loncraine]], who cast the actor in ''[[Wimbledon (film)|Wimbledon]]'' in 2004, cast him in ''[[Firewall (film)|Firewall]]'' two years later, in 2006.<ref name=\"New Amsterdam Forever\"/> In 2007, he played John Amsterdam, an immortal [[NYPD|New York]] homicide detective who will become mortal after he finds his true love, in the short-lived [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] television series ''[[New Amsterdam (2008 TV series)|New Amsterdam]]''.<ref name=\"Buddy TV\">{{cite web |url=http://www.buddytv.com/nikolaj-coster-waldau.aspx |title=Nikolaj Coster-Waldau profile |website=Buddy TV |accessdate=3 August 2008}}</ref> As a result of filming that series' pilot, Coster-Waldau obtained his [[Screen Actors Guild]] card. He later recalled in a 2015 interview in ''[[TV Guide]]'', \"Finally getting my SAG card was huge for me...I got so excited I went straight to the SAG online shop and bought four mugs with SAG logo. [I] still have those mugs!\"<ref>{{cite journal |last=Moynihan |first=Rob |date=19 January 2015 |title=How I Got My [[Screen Actors Guild|SAG]]-[[AFTRA]] Card |journal=[[TV Guide]] |page=8}}</ref>\n\n===Mainstream and critical success (2011\u2013present)===\n[[File:Nikolaj Coster-Waldau at HBOs \"Game Of Thrones\" Season 3 (Crop).jpg|thumb|right|Coster-Waldau at the premiere of the third season of ''Game of Thrones'' in March 2013]]\nFrom 2011 to 2019, Coster-Waldau played [[Jaime Lannister]] in the [[HBO]] hit series ''[[Game of Thrones]]'', based on [[George R. R. Martin]]'s best-selling ''[[A Song of Ice and Fire]]'' fantasy novel series. He commented about the character \"What's not to like about Jaime? As an actor I couldn't ask for a better role\".<ref name=\"myFanbase\"/> For his role as Jaime Lannister he has received several accolades, including [[Primetime Emmy Award]], [[Screen Actors Guild Award]], [[Critics' Choice Television Award]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2013/05/hbo-fx-lead-critics-choice-tv-awards-but-where-are-mad-men-modern-family-505822/|title=HBO, FX Lead Critics\u2019 Choice TV Awards \u2014 But Where Are \u2018Mad Men\u2019, \u2018Modern Family\u2019?|last=Team|first=The Deadline|date=2013-05-22|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=2017-05-07|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Saturn Award]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/gravity-the-hobbit-the-desolation-of-smaug-lead-saturn-awards-noms-1201120744/|title=\u2018Gravity,\u2019  \u2018The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug\u2019 Lead Saturn Awards Noms|last=Johns|first=Nikara|date=2014-02-26|work=Variety|access-date=2017-05-07|language=en-US}}</ref> and [[E! People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Award]] nominations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/477644/glee-katy-perry-lead-people-s-choice-award-nominations-2-broke-girls-kat-dennings-and-beth-behrs-to-host|title=Full List of People's Choice Awards Nominations!|work=E! Online|access-date=2017-05-07|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, he also starred alongside Sam Shepard in Mateo Gil's feature ''[[Blackthorn (film)|Blackthorn]]'', which premiered at the [[Tribeca Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribecafilm.com/filmguide/archive/512ce0901c7d76e046000756-blackthorn|title=Blackthorn {{!}} Tribeca Film Festival|website=Tribeca|access-date=2017-05-07}}</ref> Later the same year he starred in Morten Tyldum's ''[[Headhunters (film)|Headhunters]]''. The film went on to be the highest-grossing Norwegian film of all-time<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moviefone.com/2011/10/27/headhunters-norway-biggest-hit/|title=The Norwegian Film That's a Bigger Success Than 'Harry Potter' and 'Transformers'|last=Rosen|first=Christopher|date=2011-10-27|website=AOL Moviefone|access-date=2017-05-07}}</ref> and received very positive reviews including a [[BAFTA]] Award nomination for [[BAFTA Award for Best Film Not in the English Language|Best Foreign Film]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nfi.no/norskfilm/arkiv/hodejegerne-nominert-til-bafta|title=Hodejegerne nominert til BAFTA - NFI|website=www.nfi.no|access-date=2017-05-07}}</ref> Coster-Waldau starred in the 2013 horror film ''[[Mama (2013 film)|Mama]]'' alongside [[Jessica Chastain]], which then debuted at number one in the US box office<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2013&wknd=03&p=.htm|title=Weekend Box Office Results for January 18-20, 2013 - Box Office Mojo|website=www.boxofficemojo.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-07}}</ref> and grossed over $140 million worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=mama.htm|title=Mama (2013) - Box Office Mojo|website=www.boxofficemojo.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-07}}</ref> He went on to play Sykes, a military weapons expert in the [[science fiction]] [[action film|action]] [[thriller film|thriller]] film ''[[Oblivion (2013 film)|Oblivion]]''. The same year he co-starred with [[Juliette Binoche]] in Erik Poppe's drama ''[[A Thousand Times Good Night]]''. In 2014, he starred in [[Susanne Bier]]'s Danish thriller ''[[A Second Chance (film)|A Second Chance]]'' as Andreas, a police officer forced to make a difficult choice. In 2016, Coster-Waldau appeared in the action-fantasy film ''[[Gods of Egypt (film)|Gods of Egypt]]'' as [[Horus]].\n\nIn early 2017, he starred in [[E.L. Katz]]'s dark comedy ''[[Small Crimes]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/nikolaj-coster-waldau-comedy-small-crimes-1201770945/|title=Nikolaj Coster-Waldau Starring in Dark Comedy 'Small Crimes'|last=McNary|first=Dave|date=11 May 2016|journal=Variety|accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> which premiered at [[South by Southwest]] film festival on 11 March 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://schedule.sxsw.com/2017/films/71825|title=Small Crimes - SXSW 2017 Schedule|publisher=[[South by Southwest]]|access-date=March 25, 2017|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6pEr8vtRt?url=http://schedule.sxsw.com/2017/films/71825|archive-date=March 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=}}</ref> to positive reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/small_crimes/|title=Small Crimes (2017)|publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=March 25, 2017}}</ref> Coster-Waldau then appeared in the Danish film ''3 Things'', a thriller about a prime suspect of a bank robbery who negotiates the terms of his witness protection deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/game-of-thrones-nikolaj-coster-waldau-3-things-1201643375/|title='Game of Thrones' Star Nikolaj Coster-Waldau Boards Thriller '3 Things'|last=Keslassy|first=Elsa|date=18 November 2015|journal=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.dfi.dk/faktaomfilm/film/da/95761.aspx?id=95761|title=3 ting|access-date=2017-05-06}}</ref> He starred in Roman Waugh's prison film ''[[Shot Caller (film)|Shot Caller]],'' which premiered at the [[Los Angeles Film Festival]] on 16 June 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.shootonline.com/news/la-film-fests-closing-night-film-matt-spicers-ingrid-goes-west|title=LA Film Fest's Closing Night Film: Matt Spicer's \"Ingrid Goes West\"|website=SHOOTonline.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://winteriscoming.net/2015/04/26/nikolaj-coster-waldau-will-play-a-socal-gangster-in-shot-caller/ |title=Nikolaj Coster-Waldau will play a SoCal gangster in Shot Caller |first=Dan |last=Selcke |date=26 April 2015 |website=Winter is Coming |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> Since January 2018 he has been the [[L'Or\u00e9al Paris]] global spokesperson for the company's Men Expert line of products.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://brandequity.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/business-of-brands/game-of-thrones-nikolaj-coster-waldau-to-endorse-loral-paris-men-expert/62439217|title=Game of Thrones' Nikolaj Coster-Waldau to endorse LOr\u00e9al Paris Men Expert - ET BrandEquity|last=www.ETBrandEquity.com|website=ETBrandEquity.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-27}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, it was announced that he is attached to star in ''[[Domino (2018 film)|Domino]]'', a film directed by [[Brian De Palma]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cannes-nikolaj-coster-waldau-christina-hendricks-star-brian-de-palmas-domino-999691|title=Cannes: Nikolaj Coster Waldau, Christina Hendricks to Star in Brian De Palma's 'Domino' (Exclusive)|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2017-05-06|language=en}}</ref> The film was released on May 31, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://collider.com/domino-trailer-nikolaj-coster-waldau-brian-de-palma/|title=Brian De Palma's Action-Thriller 'Domino' Finally Gets a Trailer|last=Foutch|first=Haleigh|date=2019-04-04|website=Collider|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> Later the same year he starred in ''Suicide Tourist'' by Jonas Alexander Arnby, which premiered at the [[Zurich Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/joker-judy-pavarotti-get-zurich-film-festival-gala-screenings-1203322873/|title=\u2018Joker,\u2019 \u2018Judy,\u2019 and \u2018Pavarotti\u2019 Set for Zurich Film Festival Galas|last=Clarke|first=Stewart|last2=Clarke|first2=Stewart|date=2019-09-04|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-11-23}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/game-of-thrones-nikolaj-coster-waldau-jonas-arnby-suicide-tourist-1202992232/|title=\u2018Game of Thrones\u2019 Star Nikolaj Coster-Waldau Set for \u2018Suicide Tourist\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE)|last=Keslassy|first=John Hopewell, Elsa|last2=Keslassy|first2=John Hopewell, Elsa|date=2018-10-25|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2018-12-13}}</ref> Also in 2019, Coster-Waldau launched a production company named Ill Kippers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/11/game-of-thrones-nikolaj-coster-waldau-new-production-company-ya-novel-optioned-we-are-lost-and-found-jeffrey-chassen-1202793324/|title=\u2018Game Of Thrones\u2019 Nikolaj Coster-Waldau Forms Production Company; Options YA Novel \u2018We Are Lost & Found\u2019|last=Patten|first=Dominic|last2=Patten|first2=Dominic|date=2019-11-23|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-11-23}}</ref>\n\n==== Upcoming projects ====\nCoster-Waldau is set to star in ''The Silencing,'' a thriller directed by Robin Pront.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/nikolaj-coster-waldau-the-silencing-movie-cast-cannes-1202384413/|title=Nikolaj Coster-Waldau To Star In Thriller \u2018The Silencing\u2019 \u2013 Cannes|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|date=2018-05-07|work=Deadline|access-date=2018-10-20|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/after-hero-fiennes-tiffin-nikolaj-coster-waldau-annabelle-wallis-the-silencing-1202591199/|title=\u2018After\u2019 Star Hero Fiennes Tiffin Joins Nikolaj Coster-Waldau, Annabelle Wallis In \u2018The Silencing\u2019|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|last2=N'Duka|first2=Amanda|date=2019-04-08|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> He filmed in secret the upcoming movie ''Notat'' by [[Ole Christian Madsen]]. ''Notat'' is based on events surrounding the [[2015 Copenhagen shootings]] and is due for release by the end of 2019.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/325090/copenhagen-attack-film-features-game-of-thrones-star|title=Copenhagen attack film features \u2018Game of Thrones\u2019 star|website=entertainment.inquirer.net|language=en|access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> In 2020 he will portray [[Macbeth]] in a production of Shakespeare's tragedy directed by [[Matt Shakman]] at the [[Geffen Playhouse]] in Los Angeles.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/22/theater/nikolaj-coster-waldau-macbeth-geffen-playhouse.html|title=Nikolaj Coster-Waldau to Play Macbeth Onstage at the Geffen Playhouse|last=Libbey|first=Peter|date=2019-02-22|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-02-23|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nAlthough Coster-Waldau is not religious, he was baptized and confirmed as a [[Lutheran]] in the [[Danish National Church]] during his youth, like the vast majority of Danes,  and viewed his [[confirmation]] as a big moment in his life when he first identified as becoming an adult.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/24/arts/television/nikolaj-coster-waldau-the-first-time-i-recognized-my-selfishness.html|title=Nikolaj Coster-Waldau: The First Time I Recognized My Selfishness|first=Nikolaj|last=Coster-Waldau|date=24 April 2017|publisher=|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n\nHe married [[Nukaaka Coster-Waldau|Nuk\u00e2ka]], a Greenlandic actress and singer, in 1997,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.instyle.com/2014/04/03/nikolaj-coster-waldau-instyle-interview/ |title=Game of Thrones Bad Boy Nikolaj Coster-Waldau Is Actually Really Nice in Real Life |first=Katie |last=Donbavand |website=InStyle.com |date=3 April 2014 |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> and they live in [[Los Angeles]] with their two daughters<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.torontosun.com/2014/10/23/game-of-thrones-star-nikolaj-coster-waldau-promises-big-things-in-store-for-season-five |title='Game of Thrones' star Nikolaj Coster-Waldau promises big things in store for season five |newspaper=[[Toronto Sun]] |first=Steve |last=Tilley |date=23 October 2014 |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite av media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XOsjvkkKHM8|title=Her er dit liv - (Nikolaj Coster-Waldau) |date=17 December 2012 |work=YouTube |accessdate=13 July 2016 |language=Danish}}</ref> as well as two dogs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.details.com/culture-trends/cover-stars/201404/nikolaj-coster-waldau-interview-hbo-game-of-thrones-jaime-lannister/?currentPage=3 |title=Great Dane: Game of Thrones' Nikolaj Coster-Waldau |first=Benjamin |last=Svetkey |page=3 |date=1 April 2014 |website=Cond\u00e9 Nast |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150928023223/http://www.details.com/culture-trends/cover-stars/201404/nikolaj-coster-waldau-interview-hbo-game-of-thrones-jaime-lannister/?currentPage=3 |archivedate=28 September 2015 |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> Their daughter Filippa starred in a Danish [[short film]], ''The Girl and the Dogs'', which was shown at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sub.festival-cannes.fr/SfcCatalogue/MovieDetail/6d29f794-211b-4c46-ab7e-b692762201db |title=Short Film Catalog: The Girl And The Dogs |website=Festival de Cannes |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://cphfilmfund.com/the-girl-and-the-dogs/ |title=The Girl and the Dogs |website=Copenhagen Film Fund |accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> Their other daughter, Safina starred in a Danish Christmas TV-series named Theo og Den Magiske Talisman in December 2018 as the main character Simone.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9328644/ |title=Theo og Den Magiske Talisman |website=IMDB |accessdate=31 Dec 2018}}</ref> The TV-series was watched by more than 700,000 people in December 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://juleweb.dk/nyhed201832/|title=Theo og Den Magiske Talisman seertal (in Danish)|website=Juleweb.dk |accessdate=31 Dec 2018}}</ref> His father-in-law is [[Josef Motzfeldt]], a member of the [[Parliament of Greenland]] and former leader of the [[Inuit Ataqatigiit|Community of the People party]].\n\nAlthough his father is a supporter of [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], a trip to a match at the [[Elland Road]] ground in the early 1990s persuaded him to become a supporter of [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]], and he is a member of the Leeds United Supporters' Trust.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.twitter.com/LUFC/status/1115955459788349441|title=LUFC Trust on Twitter|newspaper=Twitter|access-date=2017-01-12}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, Coster-Waldau signed on to narrate one of the fairytales for [[GivingTales]], the celebrity storytelling app for children and adults alike. He is going to narrate \"[[The Steadfast Tin Soldier]]\", on which he commented, \"I am from Denmark and [[Hans Christian Andersen]] is part of our culture and I am very proud being part of this project. 'The Steadfast Tin Soldier' is a beautiful love story which we can all relate to.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lawlessent.com/blog_mod/nikolaj-coster-waldau-to-read-fairytales-for-givingtales/|title=Nikolaj Coster-Waldau to Read Fairytales for GivingTales - Lawless Entertainment|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n===UNDP ambassadorship and other humanitarian causes===\n\nCoster-Waldau has supported the [[Red Cross|Danish Red Cross]] since 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://web.drk.dk/sw2698.asp|title=Rekord for Klub 10 i 2003|work=R\u00d8DE KORS |accessdate=11 February 2017 |language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rodekors.dk/klub10/klub100|title=Klub 100|work=R\u00d8DE KORS |accessdate=11 February 2017 |language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://copenhagenagency.com/rode-kors/|title=R\u00d8DE KORS|work=copenhagenagency |accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref> In 2016, he announced a ''Game of Thrones'' campaign-contest in order to support the [[Product Red|RED]] foundation which aims to raise awareness and fight AIDS.<ref>{{cite av media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xsyRrEG3V1s|title=Game of Thrones news from Nikolaj Coster-Waldau (aka Jaime Lannister)! |date=14 January 2016 |work=YouTube |accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref>\n{{quote box|width=30em||border = 1px\n|align     = right\n|halign    = left\n|quote=\"My main mission as UNDP Goodwill Ambassador will be to raise awareness and support for the Global Goals for a better future for all, which cannot be achieved without empowering women and protecting our planet,\"|source=\u2014Coster-Waldau on his mission as [[UNDP]] Goodwill Ambassador in 2016<ref name=UNDP>{{cite web |url=http://www.undp.org/content/undp/en/home/presscenter/pressreleases/2016/09/17/game-of-thrones-star-nikolaj-coster-waldau-named-undp-goodwill-ambassador.html  |title= Game of Thrones Star Nikolaj Coster-Waldau named UNDP Goodwill Ambassador|website=undp.org|accessdate=17 July 2016}}</ref>}}\n\nSince September 2016 he has been serving as a [[UNDP]] Goodwill Ambassador to raise awareness and support the [[United Nations]]' [[Sustainable Development Goals]], an action to end poverty, fight inequality and stop climate change.<ref name=UNDP/> In 2017 Coster-Waldau partnered with [[Google]], using [[Google Street View|Street View]] to document the impact of global warming in Greenland, in order to increase awareness and highlight climate change.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://blog.google/products/maps/nikolaj-coster-waldau-documents-changing-landscape-greenland/ |title= Nikolaj Coster-Waldau documents the changing landscape of Greenland|website=blog.google|accessdate=11 February 2017}}</ref>\nAfter participating in a female empowerment initiative in [[Kenya]], on the occasion of [[International Women's Day]] in 2017, he wrote a pledge calling for all fathers to support gender equality and women's empowerment, including those women who live in extreme poverty and are exposed to practises like child marriage.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.undp.org/content/undp/en/home/blog/2017/3/8/A-father-s-pledge-for-my-daughter-and-every-daughter.html |title= A father\u2019s pledge \u2013 for my daughters and every daughter|website=undp.org|accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref> In September 2017 he was one of the speakers in The Spotlight Initiative, a [[European Union]]-[[United Nations]] action to eliminate violence against women and girls,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.un.org/en/spotlight-initiative/event.shtml|title=The Spotlight Initiative|website=www.un.org|language=en|access-date=2017-09-21}}</ref> after kicking off the women's amateur World Cup.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.undp.org/content/undp/en/home/presscenter/pressreleases/2017/09/19/game-of-thrones-star-nikolaj-coster-waldau-blows-whistle-on-poverty-at-women-s-soccer-world-cup-tournament-in-nyc.html|title=Game of Thrones star Nikolaj Coster-Waldau blows whistle on poverty at women\u2019s soccer World Cup tournament in NYC|website=UNDP|language=en|access-date=2017-09-21}}</ref> In October 2017, he travelled to the Maldives to report global warming effects, resuming his role as a United Nations Development Program Goodwill Ambassador.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.nationalgeographic.com/2017/11/nikolaj-coster-waldau-jamie-lannister-climate-change-united-nations/|title=Game of Thrones Star Sounds the Alarm on Climate Change|date=2017-11-06|access-date=2018-01-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mv.undp.org/content/maldives/en/home/presscenter/articles/2016successstories1/UNDPGoodwillAmbassadorNikolajCosterWaldaukicksoffMaldivesClimateActionJourney.html|title=UNDP Goodwill Ambassador, Nikolaj Coster-Waldau kicks off Maldives' Climate Action Journey|website=UNDP in Maldives|language=en|access-date=2018-01-27}}</ref>\n\nIn early 2018, he and several other Danish artists signed a manifesto demanding zero tolerance for sexism, sexual harassment and sexual assault in the Danish film and stage arts industry.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/kultur/film/over-tusind-film-og-teaterfolk-i-danmark-underskriver-manifest-mod-sexisme-og|title=Over tusind film- og teaterfolk i Danmark underskriver manifest mod sexisme og overgreb|work=DR|access-date=2018-01-27|language=da}}</ref> In June 2018, he kicked off The Lion's Share fund's launch, an action in which when an advertising campaign uses an image of an animal, the advertiser will donate 0.5% of the paid media spending of that campaign to the fund.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.undp.org/content/undp/en/home/news-centre/news/2018/undp-announces-the-lion-s-share-fund-with-founder-finch-and-foun1.html|title=UNDP announces The Lion's Share fund with founder FINCH and founding partner Mars to tackle crisis in wildlife conservation and animal welfare {{!}} UNDP|website=UNDP|language=en|access-date=2018-09-29}}</ref> In 2019 he travelled to [[Rwanda]] to report the progress of the country, and to [[Peruvian Amazonia]] on occasion of the [[2019 Amazon rainforest wildfires|Amazon rainforest wildfires]] to offer insights into the effects of climate change.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.undp.org/content/undp/en/home/news-centre/news/2019/Game_of_Thrones_star_UNDP_Goodwill_Ambassador_Nikolaj_Coster_Waldau_Rwanda.html|title=Game of Thrones star and UNDP Goodwill Ambassador Nikolaj Coster-Waldau visits Rwanda 25 years after genocide against the Tutsi|website=UNDP|language=en|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.undp.org/content/undp/en/home/news-centre/news/2019/Nikolaj_Coster_Waldau_Amazon_UNDP_fires.html|title=Game of Thrones star Nikolaj Coster-Waldau travels to the Amazon with UNDP to discover the real story behind the fires|website=UNDP|language=en|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Role\n! scope=\"col\"| Director\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| 1994\n! scope=row | ''[[Nightwatch (1994 film)|Nightwatch]]''\n| Martin Bork\n| [[Ole Bornedal]]\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |1997\n! scope=row | ''[[Bent (1997 film)|Bent]]''\n| Wolf\n| [[Sean Mathias]]\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n! scope=row | ''Hemmeligheder''\n| Mads\n|J\u00f8rn Faurschou\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |1998\n! scope=row | ''Wildside''\n| Ossy\n|[[Simon Staho]]\n| Also writer\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n! scope=row | ''Nattens engel''\n| Frankie\n| Shaky Gonz\u00e1lez\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |1999\n! scope=row | ''The Cable Club''\n| Rocker\n| S\u00f8ren Fauli\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n! scope=row | ''[[Misery Harbour]]''\n| Espen Arnakke\n| [[Nils Gaup]]\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| 2000\n! scope=row | ''P\u00e5 fremmed mark''\n| 